title: The Fat Spy (1966, Comedy film) Jayne Mansfield, Phyllis Diller, & The Wild Ones

sources.title: The Fat Spy (1966, Comedy film) Jayne Mansfield, Phyllis Diller, & The Wild Ones
sources.description:
It's a killer... a Diller... a blast of laffs!  Off the coast of Florida, a nearly-deserted island is rumored to have the fountain of youth. A boatload of youths are headed there for a scavenger hunt.

Original title: The Fat Spy (1966)
This film is subtitled in many language options.

Director: Joseph Cates
Writer: Matthew Andrews 
Stars: Phyllis Diller, Jack E. Leonard, Brian Donlevy, Jayne Mansfield & The Wild Ones
Genres: 60s Movies, Comedy, Musical, B-movie


00:00 A group of teenagers arrives on a mysterious island, sparking a treasure hunt.
06:08 Junior learns about the teens' arrival and vows to investigate their intentions.
13:40 Camille Salamander schemes to exploit the mythical Fountain of Youth for profit.
24:35 Irving and Junior share a heartfelt moment, deepening their connection.
45:00 Irving uncovers a vital clue about the Spanish shipwreck and its hidden treasure.
57:23 The Fountain of Youth is revealed to be hidden in plain sight at Wellington's estate.
69:50 The truth about the black twin roses, the key to eternal youth, is uncovered.
76:33 Irving and Junior confront Camille and Herman, leading to a surprising resolution.
